To implement a condition that checks for an advancement in MCreator, you can follow these steps:

1. Open the "Check Pickaxe Usage" procedure you created earlier.
2. Drag and drop the "Run procedure in Minecraft code" block into the procedure editor.
3. You can use the following code snippet to check if a player has a specific advancement:

```
AdvancementManager advancementManager = Minecraft.getInstance().player.connection.getAdvancementManager();
Advancement advancement = advancementManager.getAdvancement(new ResourceLocation("namespace:advancement_name"));
if (advancement != null && Minecraft.getInstance().player.getAdvancements().getProgress(advancement).isDone()) {
    // Player has the required advancement
} else {
    // Player doesn't have the required advancement
}
```

Replace "namespace" with the namespace of the advancement and "advancement_name" with the ID of the advancement. For example, if the advancement you want to check for is called "Mastery," and it has a namespace of "my_awesome_mod," the code will be:

```
AdvancementManager advancementManager = Minecraft.getInstance().player.connection.getAdvancementManager();
Advancement advancement = advancementManager.getAdvancement(new ResourceLocation("my_awesome_mod:mastery"));
if (advancement != null && Minecraft.getInstance().player.getAdvancements().getProgress(advancement).isDone()) {
    // Player has the required advancement
} else {
    // Player doesn't have the required advancement
}
```

4. Drag and drop the appropriate blocks into the "if" and "else" sections depending on the condition's result.

This will check whether the player has a particular advancement and allow or disallow the player from using the specified tool accordingly. Note that this code needs to be added to the mod's code directly instead of using the MCreator interface. You can access the "code" tab in your mod to add this code. Additionally, be sure to test your mod thoroughly to confirm that it works as intended.
